^-|CP||FP||AT|^B@2^Y@3- Howard would you please briefly explain what is all about this Inverted minors?|
PG| ***** 144 ***** |


cp|8|AT|

^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Inverted minors basically "invert" the strength of 2 level and 3 level raises. If not playing inverted minor raises, a raise to 2 is weaker than a raise to 3. However, if you play inverted raises, a raise to 2 is stronger than a raise to 3. There are more details that I need to explain, but that is the essence of the convention. The justification is that with a weak hand you want to preempt the opponent as soon as possible, whereas with a stronger hand you want to retain more room to explore for the appropriate contract.|
