PG| ***** 157 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If responder has a game forcing hand, he must make sure the partnership bids game, by either bidding 3N if all suits are stopped, or continue bidding new suits if not. Similarly, if opener has 15+, it is his responsibility to make sure the partnership reaches games, by either bidding 3N if all suits are stopped, or continuing to bid new suits if not. Once 3 suits have been bid (the original suit and 2 stopper suits), if someone bids the 4th suit, that is asking about a stopper rather than telling, because if the bidder has the remaining suit stopped, he can bid NT himself.|
