^-|CP||FP||AT|^B@2^Y@3- In standard response to 1m opening the second priority is to bid NT in various levels based on strength of the hand. In general the responder ends up playing the hand in NT. How does Inverted Minors change the bidding?|
PG| ***** 159 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Generally, inverted minors do not affect 2N and 3N bids by responder. Responder makes these 2 bids using the same criteria, whether or not he is playing inverted minors. Inverted minors do have a small effect on the 1N bid by responder. Not playing inverted minors, responder may occasionally raise to 2 with 4 card support, rather than bidding 1N. However, playing inverted minors, responder cannot make a weak raise to 3 unless he has 5 card support, so he is forced to bid 1N on some hands where he might have made a raise otherwise.|
